The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Private Sector's Practices</ENAMEX>
According to the results of <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">three</NUMEX> recent surveys, the private
sector commonly allows its <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">employees</ENAMEX> to retain for personal use
frequent flyer miles received on business travel. This <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">practice</ENAMEX> may
give the private sector, including government <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">contractors</ENAMEX>, an
advantage over the federal <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">government</ENAMEX> in recruiting and retaining
